The Health Department has reported 1 862 new cases of coronavirus, taking the number of total infections to 1 507 448. There have been a further 110 COVID-19-related deaths in the country, bringing the national death toll to 49 523 deaths. In a statement, Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize says most of the new deaths were recorded in the Free State. “Regrettably, we report 110 more COVID-19 related deaths: 5 from Eastern Cape, 61 from the Free State, 12 from Gauteng, 7 from KwaZulu-Natal, 0 from Limpopo, 7 from Mpumalanga, 0 from North West, 1 from Northern Cape and 17 from the Western Cape,” says Dr Mkhize. Recoveries now stand at 1 422 622, representing a recovery rate of 94%. As of today, the total number of confirmed #COVID19 cases is 1 507 448 the total number of deaths is 49 523, the total number of recoveries is 1 422 622 and the total number of vaccines administered is 41 809. pic.twitter.com/fSuGPvaBDT — Dr Zweli Mkhize (@DrZweliMkhize) February 24, 2021 